    "content": "Computer hardware comprises the physical parts of a computer system.\n\n*   **Central Processing Unit (CPU):** The 'brain' of the computer, executing instructions.\n*   **Random Access Memory (RAM):**  Volatile memory used for temporary data storage, as highlighted in the \"RAM vs. Storage\" interactive coding exercise.\n*   **Storage Devices:**  Non-volatile memory for permanent data storage (e.g., SSDs, HDDs).\n*   **Motherboard:** The main circuit board connecting all components.\n*   **Graphics Processing Unit (GPU):** Handles image and video processing.\n*   **Input Devices:** Allow you to interact with the computer (e.g., keyboard, mouse).\n*   **Output Devices:** Display or present information (e.g., monitor, printer)."
